rict 2|2018]]<ref name=\"NV02\">{{cite web |last1=Dornan |first1=Geoff |title=FILING FINAL: Kramer out, O\u2019Neill in for Carson City Assembly race |url=https://www.nevadaappeal.com/news/carson-citys-al-kramer-withdraws-from-race-to-retain-assembly-seat/ |website=Nevada Appeal |date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=====Declined=====\n*[[Heidi Gansert]], state senator<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\" />\n*[[Ben Kieckhefer]], state senator<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\" />\n*[[Adam Laxalt]], former [[Nevada Attorney General]] and candidate for [[Governor of Nevada]] in [[2018 Nevada gubernatorial election|2018]]<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\" />\n*[[James Settelmeyer]], minority leader of the [[Nevada Senate]]<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\" />\n*[[Danny Tarkanian]], attorney, businessman and perennial candidate<ref>{{cite news|last1=Messerly|first1=Megan|last2=Rindels|first2=Michelle|title=Amodei not worried about primary challengers, invites anyone with \u2018a better mousetrap\u2019 to get in|url=https://thenevadaindependent.com/article/amodei-not-worried-about-primary-challengers-invites-anyone-with-a-better-mousetrap-to-get-in|publisher=The Nevada Independent|date=April 17, 2019|accessdate=April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jim Wheeler]], minority leader of the [[Nevada Assembly]]<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\" />\n\n====Polling====\n{{collapse top|1=<span style=\"font-size:88%;\">Hypothetical polling</span>|left=yes|bg=#B0CEFF;line-height:135%;|border=none}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;text-align:center;\"\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size{{efn|name=key|Key:<br>A \u2013 all adults<br>RV \u2013 registered voters<br>LV \u2013 likely voters<br>V \u2013 unclear}}\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Mark Amodei\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Adam Laxalt\n! Undecided\n|-\n| rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://www.clubforgrowth.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/CFG_NV_CD2_IVR_Poll_Memo_191023.pdf WPA Intelligence/Club for Growth]{{efn-