ection box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate =  Robert Van Strawder \n| party = Libertarian Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate =  Joseph Maridon\n| party = Independent (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==District 2==\n{{see also|Nevada's 2nd congressional district}}\nThe 2nd district covers much of northern Nevada, including [[Reno, Nevada|Reno]], [[Sparks, Nevada|Sparks]] and [[Carson City, Nevada|Carson City]]. The incumbent is Republican [[Mark Amodei]], who was re-elected with 58.2% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Declared=====\n*[[Mark Amodei]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\">{{cite news|last1=Ralston|first1=Jon|title=Amodei: Come on in, the water's fine|url=https://thenevadaindependent.com/article/amodei-come-on-in-the-waters-fine|publisher=The Nevada Independent|date=March 4, 2019|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n*Joel Beck, U.S. Air Force veteran and candidate for Nevada's 2nd congressional district in [[2018 United States House of Representatives elections in Nevada#District 2|2018]]<ref name=\"NV02\">{{cite web |last1=Dornan |first1=Geoff |title=FILING FINAL: Kramer out, O\u2019Neill in for Carson City Assembly race |url=https://www.nevadaappeal.com/news/carson-citys-al-kramer-withdraws-from-race-to-retain-assembly-seat/ |website=Nevada Appeal |date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=====Declined=====\n*[[Heidi Gansert]], state senator<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\" />\n*[[Ben Kieckhefer]], state senator<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\" />\n*[[Adam Laxalt]], former [[Nevada Attorney General]] and candidate for [[Governor of Nevada]] in [[2018 Nevada gubernatorial election|2018]]<ref name=\"NV02Ralston\" />\n*[[James Settelmeyer]], minority leader of the [[Nevada Senate]]<ref name=\"NV02